article.description: DJ Williams scored 14 points, Terry Nolan added 12 points and 10 rebounds and George Washington bounced back from a miserable first half to take a 59-56 victory over La Salle on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Colonials recover from poor first half to win 59-56
article.linkText: Colonials recover from poor first half to win 59-56
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- DJ Williams scored 14 points, Terry Nolan added 12 points and 10 rebounds and George Washington bounced back from a miserable first half to take a 59-56 victory over La Salle on Wednesday night. Justin Mazzulla added 11 points and Maceo Jack 10 for the Colonials (6-11, 2-2 Atlantic 10), who have won four of their last five games. After shooting just 16 percent and trailing 23-14 at halftime, the Colonials bounced back to shoot 68 percent in the second half. Isiah Deas was the lone double-figure scorer for the Explorers with 11 points. La Salle (3-13, 1-3), winless in seven home games this season, made just 5 of 32 from the arc. George Washington took its first lead of the second half, 55-53, on Jack's 3-pointer with 2:05 left. La Salle retook the lead on Jaren Kimbrough's 3-point play before Armel Potter's basket gave the lead back to the Colonials with 1:10 remaining. Nolan added two free throws with 20 seconds left.
